page.title: 07Flora & Fauna,Nw Essex
page.content: In Stebbing there are lots of rare and beautiful birds, animals and plants. Here is a small list of rare and attractive birds seen.They are kingfisher,green woodpecker,brambling, grey wagtail,sedge warbler,stonechat, grasshopper warbler,{hoopoe,}wheatear, nightingale and little owl.There are 81 kinds of birds in Stebbing. There are 34 kinds of wild plants in Stebbing including many wild flowers like dog violet,meadow sweet,cowslips and dog rose. The Bardfield oxlip has also been found. Animals seen in Stebbing are badgers foxes,roe deer and Muntjac deer.There are 78 different moths including four kinds of hawk moth.There are seven kinds of butterflies including Marbled White,Wall Brown,Speckled Wood,Small Tortoise shell,Red Admiral,Peacock and Orange Tip.
